<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1874-10-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1874-10-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="347" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d347">
                    <head>No. 345.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Fish</persName>
                            to Sir <persName type="to">Edward Thornton</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1874-10-27"><hi rend="italic">October</hi> 27,
                            1874</date>.</dateline></opener>
                    <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                        your note of yesterday’s date, in which you are pleased to state, in answer
                        to the inquiry of this Department, that the whole of Labrador outside of the
                        province of Quebec, is under the jurisdiction and government of the colony
                        of Newfoundland, and is actually included in and forms a part of that
                        colony.</p>
                    <p>Thanking you for this information,</p>
                    <p>I have. &amp;c.,</p>
                    <closer><signed>HAMILTON FISH.</signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>